Schwartzel has struggled of late with injury and has seen his world ranking plummet to 125th. Schwartzel's withdrawal leaves eighth South Africans in the 156-man field for the year's second Major to be played at Bethpage Black in New York, starting on Thursday. The last time a South African lifted the famed Wanamaker Trophy was in 1972 when Gary Player won by two strokes for his second PGA Championship title.

